# Plan Gate Review — ai-chatbot-for-customer-support

## Evaluation

**Completeness check:**
- All 5 client requirements mapped to concrete demo features with file-level traceability. ✅
- Architecture specifies exact CDN URLs, model IDs, and package versions (no "TBD" gaps). ✅
  - WebLLM: `https://esm.run/@mlc-ai/web-llm` v0.2.84, model `Llama-3.2-1B-Instruct-q4f16_1-MLC` confirmed.
  - Transformers.js: `https://cdn.jsdelivr.net/npm/@huggingface/transformers@4.2.0/+esm`, `onnx-community/Qwen2.5-0.5B-Instruct` q4/wasm, `Xenova/all-MiniLM-L6-v2` fp32/wasm confirmed.
  - Package rename noted: `@xenova/transformers` is frozen/EOL — do NOT use.
- LLM fallback chain fully defined: WebLLM → Transformers.js WASM → template-RAG. ✅
- CI/Playwright constraint explicitly handled: WASM path confirmed as primary tested path. ✅
- Research questions all marked answered (✅ on all 5); FAQ corpus sourced verbatim from pre-researcher.out. ✅
- Design system fully specified (hex values, fonts, spacing, bubble styles). ✅
- 12-file manifest at the 12-file cap. ✅
- Timeline, pricing, and fixed-vs-hourly recommendation present. ✅
- Plan explicitly self-declares READY: "Plan status: READY — all research integrated, build can proceed." ✅

**Flagged unknowns check:**
- Transformers.js v4 pipeline API difference: flagged as a builder risk with directive to test against confirmed snippet. Actionable, not blocking. ✅
- WASM latency (3-8s): mitigated by typing indicator directive. ✅
- WebGPU 600-900 MB download: mitigated by progress bar + IndexedDB caching UX directive. ✅
- No unresolved unknowns requiring additional research.

**Problems found:** None.

VERDICT: pass

